260
00:12:33,453 --> 00:12:35,945
I didn't say that.

261
00:12:50,937 --> 00:12:52,462
Hey.

262
00:12:52,505 --> 00:12:55,531
They don't all have to
be white lights, you know.

263
00:12:55,775 --> 00:12:58,801
Well, that's the way
Mom always used to do it.

264
00:12:58,845 --> 00:13:01,246
That doesn't mean
it's set in stone.

265
00:13:01,281 --> 00:13:04,012
Nothing really is.

266
00:13:04,050 --> 00:13:05,313
We still talking
about the lights,

267
00:13:05,351 --> 00:13:07,445
or we talking about
how I run the ranch?

268
00:13:07,487 --> 00:13:10,286
Something has to give, son.

269
00:13:10,323 --> 00:13:12,792
I know it's not your fault
that we're in this pinch.

270
00:13:12,825 --> 00:13:15,487
Everyone's trying to recover
from the drought.

271
00:13:15,528 --> 00:13:20,261
But... we really need that
second loan, you know?

272
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,495
Yeah.

273
00:13:21,534 --> 00:13:24,504
I know it's tough
being the bad guy.

274
00:13:24,537 --> 00:13:25,971
Butif it's a decision between

275
00:13:26,005 --> 00:13:27,973
laying people off
and losing everything--

276
00:13:28,007 --> 00:13:30,101
No, we're not laying anyone off.

277
00:13:30,143 --> 00:13:32,134
I'd prefer to sell
part of the land.

278
00:13:32,178 --> 00:13:34,875
Okay then.

279
00:13:34,914 --> 00:13:35,938
Okay.

280
00:13:35,982 --> 00:13:40,146
Can't hurt to hear
Sara's ideas.

281
00:13:40,186 --> 00:13:42,416
And then, you're gonna have
to make a tough choice,

282
00:13:42,455 --> 00:13:45,481
just like you did
when you moved back here.

283
00:13:45,525 --> 00:13:47,323
Ah, that wasn't a tough choice.

284
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:49,488
I only moved away
because I wanted to try

285
00:13:49,529 --> 00:13:51,998
something completely
different from this life.

286
00:13:52,031 --> 00:13:53,556
(chuckling)

287
00:13:53,599 --> 00:13:56,398
Well, corporate law is just
about as different as it gets.

288
00:13:56,436 --> 00:13:59,167
(chuckling)
Yes, itis.

289
00:13:59,205 --> 00:14:02,436
But after a while, I realized
I not only left home,

290
00:14:02,475 --> 00:14:05,274
I left who I was.

291
00:14:05,311 --> 00:14:08,576
My only regret is not
coming home sooner,

292
00:14:08,614 --> 00:14:11,083
so I could spend
more time with Mom.

293
00:14:11,117 --> 00:14:14,951
Now, there's nothing you
could've done for Mom back then.

294
00:14:14,987 --> 00:14:16,978
And now, you're keeping
her Christmas traditions

295
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:19,082
alive and well.

296
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:24,463
But son, this ranch
is running on fumes.

297
00:14:24,497 --> 00:14:28,127
You gotta make some changes
or accept the fact

298
00:14:28,167 --> 00:14:31,501
that this could be the last
Christmas we spend here.

299
00:14:38,344 --> 00:14:41,473
(sighin
9
See?

300
00:14:41,514 --> 00:14:43,949
Sometimes changing things up...

301
00:14:43,983 --> 00:14:47,112
makes what you
already have better.

302
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:51,983
The lights are a metaphor.

303
00:14:52,024 --> 00:14:54,118
Oh, I get it, Dad.

304
00:14:56,529 --> 00:14:59,521
And, uh, I hear you.

305
00:15:01,968 --> 00:15:03,458
I know you do.

306
00:15:03,503 --> 00:15:04,971
(horn honking)

307
00:15:13,179 --> 00:15:15,341
{car door closing)

308
00:15:15,381 --> 00:15:16,610
Morning.

309
00:15:16,649 --> 00:15:18,310
Morning.

310
00:15:18,351 --> 00:15:20,319
Pops said it was okay
if I brought Chloe

311
00:15:20,353 --> 00:15:21,582
because Lexie's here.

312
00:15:21,621 --> 00:15:23,680
Yeah, that's fine.

313
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:25,948
Uh, she's around back
with the chickens.

314
00:15:25,992 --> 00:15:28,051
Do they like
Christmas carols, too?

315
00:15:28,094 --> 00:15:29,687
They're more into Classic Rock.

316
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:32,296
Have fun.

317
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:37,397
Look, I meant everything
that I said yesterday.

318
00:15:37,437 --> 00:15:39,701
But, uh...

319
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:42,431
I suppose I need
to let you do your job.

320
00:15:44,076 --> 00:15:47,410
I talked some sense into him.

321
00:15:47,447 --> 00:15:49,279
I owe you one.

322
00:15:53,419 --> 00:15:55,046
Well, come on, let's goin.

323
00:15:55,087 --> 00:15:57,454
After you.

324
00:16:02,161 --> 00:16:04,061
Your timing's perfect -

325
00:16:04,096 --> 00:16:07,122
Kay just dropped off some
of her candy cane cocoa.

326
00:16:07,166 --> 00:16:08,099
Kay from the B&B?

327
00:16:08,134 --> 00:16:09,465
Yeah, she's an old friend.

328
00:16:09,502 --> 00:16:11,470
She's always bringing by her
home cooking from the inn.

329
00:16:11,504 --> 00:16:14,030
Wow.
That's really nice of her.

330
00:16:14,073 --> 00:16:17,338
Oh, people in town are always
coming by here at Christmas.

331
00:16:17,376 --> 00:16:20,311
Kay comes over a little
more often than most.

332
00:16:20,346 --> 00:16:23,213
Have a seat.
I'll get you some cocoa.

333
00:16:23,249 --> 00:16:24,614
Oh, can I get that to go?

334
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:26,209
I'd really like
to get started.

335
00:16:26,252 --> 00:16:27,742
Can we go into your office
and dig into the books?

336
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:29,250
Easy there.

337
00:16:29,288 --> 00:16:30,585
You don't walk through
someone's front door

338
00:16:30,623 --> 00:16:33,183
and get straight to business.

339
00:16:33,226 --> 00:16:34,523
You're on Montana time.

340
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:36,494
What does that mean?

341
00:16:36,529 --> 00:16:40,466
That means, here,
we don't rush things,

342
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:42,195
especially at Christmas.

343
00:16:42,235 --> 00:16:45,671
We take our time to sit
and chat and eat cookies

344
00:16:45,705 --> 00:16:47,571
and drink candy cane cocoa.

345
00:16:47,607 --> 00:16:49,200
Then, we start.
Thank you.

346
00:16:49,242 --> 00:16:51,438
Oh, is that a
showman-shaped marshmallow?

347
00:16:51,477 --> 00:16:53,775
Yeah, Kay makes them
special for the bonfire

348
00:16:54,013 --> 00:16:57,608
and she gives me
any extras, of course.

349
00:16:57,650 --> 00:16:59,175
So, do you sell the
cocoa at the bonfire?

350
00:16:59,218 --> 00:17:01,312
Of course not.
They're friends.

351
00:17:01,354 --> 00:17:03,721
Oh, and she dropped
by some sausage rolls.

352
00:17:03,756 --> 00:17:05,588
Or have you already tried
them at the inn?

353
00:17:05,625 --> 00:17:09,220
Actually, I'm a vegetarian.

354
00:17:09,262 --> 00:17:11,754
Oh, well, we won't
hold that against you.

355
00:17:11,797 --> 00:17:14,391
I'll go see if the girls
want some cocoa.

356
00:17:14,433 --> 00:17:17,459
I'm really glad that
Chloe's found a friend.

357
00:17:17,503 --> 00:17:20,473
It's not easy being
an only child,

358
00:17:20,506 --> 00:17:21,735
especially when it's just
the two of us now.

359
00:17:21,774 --> 00:17:23,299
Travis:
I bet.

360
00:17:23,342 --> 00:17:25,106
How 'bout you? Any kids?

361
00:17:25,144 --> 00:17:27,704
Always wanted to, yeah.

362
00:17:27,747 --> 00:17:29,579
Christmas with my parents

363
00:17:29,615 --> 00:17:31,709
was probably
the best time of my life.

364
00:17:31,751 --> 00:17:33,742
But, uh...

365
00:17:33,786 --> 00:17:36,153
sometimes things don't work out
the way that you planned.

366
00:17:36,188 --> 00:17:39,158
Yeah, Chloe and I
know that firsthand.

367
00:17:41,727 --> 00:17:45,061
The other thing I know is that
we have a lot of work to do.

368
00:17:45,097 --> 00:17:47,191
Wow.
That was a terrible segue.

369
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:48,223
-Wasn'tit?
- Mm-hmm.

370
00:17:48,267 --> 00:17:49,632
But seriously,

371
00:17:49,669 --> 00:17:52,798
I'd like to start by digging
into last year's cash flow.

372
00:17:52,838 --> 00:17:54,499
Have you finished your cocoa?

373
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:56,634
No.

374
00:17:56,676 --> 00:17:58,269
You know the rules.

375
00:17:58,311 --> 00:18:00,302
You're not going to
make this easy, are you?

376
00:18:00,346 --> 00:18:02,542
Nothing worth doing ever is.

377
00:18:02,582 --> 00:18:03,708
Fine.

378
00:18:11,657 --> 00:18:12,783
Ready?

379
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:16,759
I reckon I am.

380
00:18:16,796 --> 00:18:17,854
Great. Let's get started.

381
00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:19,428
This way.

382
00:18:26,172 --> 00:18:28,539
(horse whinnying)

383
00:18:32,345 --> 00:18:34,404
Is this your office?

384
00:18:34,447 --> 00:18:36,472
No, this is a barn.
(chuckling)

385
00:18:36,515 --> 00:18:37,812
I just wanted to
give you a little tour

386
00:18:37,850 --> 00:18:39,614
before you bury
yourself in the numbers.

387
00:18:39,652 --> 00:18:42,349
The ranch is about a lot more
than just what's on paper.

388
00:18:46,726 --> 00:18:48,592
This is beautiful.
How old is it?

389
00:18:48,628 --> 00:18:49,891
About 150 years.

390
00:18:50,129 --> 00:18:52,723
Sara: So, what do you do
with it at Christmas?

391
00:18:52,765 --> 00:18:54,494
We host the annual
Christmas potluck,

392
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:56,661
and until then,
it's usually storage.

393
00:18:56,702 --> 00:18:58,670
I hate to tell you this,
but you've been robbed.

394
00:18:58,704 --> 00:19:01,264
Well, we haven't set it up yet.

395
00:19:01,307 --> 00:19:03,605
We have eight days
until Christmas Eve,

396
00:19:03,643 --> 00:19:05,475
and by then, this entire barn

397
00:19:05,511 --> 00:19:06,808
is gonna be
a Christmas wonderland.

398
00:19:06,846 --> 00:19:09,144
Everybody pitches in

399
00:19:09,181 --> 00:19:10,876
to set up the tables,
and the centerpieces,

400
00:19:10,916 --> 00:19:13,283
and even a stage for musicians.

401
00:19:13,319 --> 00:19:15,515
That sounds expensive.

402
00:19:15,554 --> 00:19:17,784
So, what's the overhead
on this dinner?

403
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:20,793
Zero.
Everybody pitches in.

404
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:24,456
Have you ever considered
renting this place out

405
00:19:24,497 --> 00:19:26,864
for weddings or special events?

406
00:19:26,899 --> 00:19:28,560
That's not what
this place is for.

407
00:19:28,601 --> 00:19:29,762
Could be.

408
00:19:31,737 --> 00:19:32,863
Ahh...

409
00:19:32,905 --> 00:19:35,499
Wow.

410
00:19:35,541 --> 00:19:37,635
Right? My mom collected these

411
00:19:37,677 --> 00:19:40,476
over all the years our family
hosted the Christmas potluck.

412
00:19:40,513 --> 00:19:43,881
When she passed, I promised her
that I would keep it going.

413
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:46,408
I do hope this
isn't the last one.

414
00:19:46,452 --> 00:19:49,251
I've already thought of a
couple of ways to cut costs.

415
00:19:49,288 --> 00:19:51,586
Well, if those ways involve our
Christmas traditions,

416
00:19:51,624 --> 00:19:52,785
you can forget it.

417
00:19:52,825 --> 00:19:56,659
I would never ask anyone
to give up Christmas

418
00:19:56,696 --> 00:19:59,859
Isn't that what you're doing?

419
00:19:59,899 --> 00:20:03,460
I'm doing my job,
and I'm gonna need your help.

420
00:20:03,502 --> 00:20:07,632
And you'll get it...

421
00:20:07,673 --> 00:20:10,404
...right after I do my job.

422
00:20:22,488 --> 00:20:25,219
Are you going
all the way up there?

423
00:20:25,257 --> 00:20:26,782
Well, unless you want to.

424
00:20:26,826 --> 00:20:28,521
Maybe you could have
one of the ranch hands do it

425
00:20:28,561 --> 00:20:29,824
and we could
go back to your office.

426
00:20:29,862 --> 00:20:31,455
Oh, they're out getting feed,

427
00:20:31,497 --> 00:20:32,987
or moving the cattle, making
sure the pipes are flowing...

428
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:35,963
What are you writing down?

429
00:20:36,001 --> 00:20:38,800
This is just valuable
information

430
00:20:38,838 --> 00:20:41,000
about your
day-to-day operations.

431
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:43,732
Well, outside of Christmas,
on any given day,

432
00:20:43,776 --> 00:20:46,245
I'd be working
right alongside them.

433
00:20:46,278 --> 00:20:47,905
Okay.

434
00:20:47,947 --> 00:20:50,917
You write that down.
That's important.

435
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:53,009
That's a cowboy's worth ethic.

436
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:54,481
You wouldn't ask anyone
to do anything

437
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:55,578
you wouldn't do yourself.

438
00:20:55,621 --> 00:20:58,750
Got it.

439
00:21:00,459 --> 00:21:01,688
What?

440
00:21:01,727 --> 00:21:03,559
Just seems like a waste
of perfectly nice garland

441
00:21:03,596 --> 00:21:05,530
to put it all the way
up in the rafters.

442
00:21:05,564 --> 00:21:09,000
Oh.
Well, what do you suggest?

443
00:21:09,034 --> 00:21:12,732
Well, a few years ago,

444
00:21:12,772 --> 00:21:15,639
we did this zig-zag with garland

445
00:21:15,674 --> 00:21:17,642
to look like a Christmas tree
all the way up the wall.

446
00:21:17,676 --> 00:21:20,976
We threaded in some lights

447
00:21:21,013 --> 00:21:23,710
and we put a star on top.
It was really beautiful.

448
00:21:23,749 --> 00:21:28,311
Okay. That sounds interesting.
You have any pictures?

449
00:21:28,354 --> 00:21:31,881
Um, I don't know,
that's going back a while.

450
00:21:31,924 --> 00:21:34,450
We've tried to keep
Christmas pretty low-key

451
00:21:34,493 --> 00:21:37,292
since my husband passed away.

452
00:21:37,329 --> 00:21:40,765
Oh. I... didn't know.

453
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:42,825
I'm sorry.
How long ago was it?

454
00:21:42,868 --> 00:21:44,996
Four years.

455
00:21:45,037 --> 00:21:48,029
Sometimes it seems
like a lifetime

456
00:21:48,073 --> 00:21:52,408
and sometimes it seems
like just yesterday.

457
00:21:53,879 --> 00:21:56,473
If this is too hard,
we can go back to the office

458
00:21:56,515 --> 00:21:58,313
and do what you
need to get done.

459
00:21:58,350 --> 00:21:59,613
No, I'm okay.

460
00:21:59,652 --> 00:22:01,086
Let's do that tree.

461
00:22:02,855 --> 00:22:04,482
Okay.

462
00:22:04,523 --> 00:22:05,490
Right.

463
00:22:05,524 --> 00:22:06,616
Um, actually...

464
00:22:06,659 --> 00:22:08,423
So, garland...

465
00:22:08,460 --> 00:22:09,586
...this would be perfect.

466
00:22:09,628 --> 00:22:10,686
Yep, okay.

467
00:22:10,729 --> 00:22:11,958
This is not gonna take
any time at all.

468
00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:13,465
Oh my gosh.

469
00:22:13,499 --> 00:22:15,627
Hey, what do you
think about this?

470
00:22:15,668 --> 00:22:16,692
That's a great call.

471
00:22:16,735 --> 00:22:19,329
We can do, like,
you know, on your back.

472
00:22:19,371 --> 00:22:20,668
I'm excited about
just getting going, so...

473
00:22:20,706 --> 00:22:22,572
I think you're low-key about it.

474
00:22:22,608 --> 00:22:23,632
I'm fired up.

475
00:22:23,676 --> 00:22:24,837
Okay. Good.

476
00:22:30,382 --> 00:22:31,543
Whoa!
I'm fine.

477
00:22:31,584 --> 00:22:32,745
I can see that.

478
00:22:32,785 --> 00:22:34,082
And you will be, too.

479
00:22:34,119 --> 00:22:35,746
Thank you. I mean, this ranch

480
00:22:35,788 --> 00:22:38,450
means the world
to my family and me.

481
00:22:38,490 --> 00:22:40,584
I can see that.

482
00:22:40,626 --> 00:22:43,527
Okay. You should do honors.
Here you go.

483
00:22:43,562 --> 00:22:44,825
Okay.

484
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:48,932
You were right.

485
00:22:48,968 --> 00:22:50,094
It looks amazing.
Thank you.

486
00:22:50,135 --> 00:22:51,728
You're welcome.

487
00:22:51,770 --> 00:22:54,603
And now there's plenty of time
to go over your expenses.

488
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:57,075
Wow. Wow.

489
00:22:57,109 --> 00:23:00,670
You jumped back to work mode
so fast, it gives me whiplash.

490
00:23:13,726 --> 00:23:16,491
It's been a long time since
I saw snow fall.

491
00:23:16,528 --> 00:23:18,553
When was the last time
it snowed in Los Angles?

492
00:23:18,597 --> 00:23:20,429
Um, twenty years ago.

493
00:23:20,466 --> 00:23:23,492
Snowed just enough to
make everything white...

494
00:23:23,535 --> 00:23:25,799
for about an hour.

495
00:23:25,838 --> 00:23:28,034
Hopefully this'll stick
around a little longer.

496
00:23:32,444 --> 00:23:34,708
(sighing)
Let's go.

497
00:23:38,784 --> 00:23:39,910
(sighing)

498
00:23:42,788 --> 00:23:43,949
Hey.

499
00:23:43,989 --> 00:23:45,855
First time seeing snow, huh?

500
00:23:45,891 --> 00:23:47,985
Unless you count
the sledding hill

501
00:23:48,027 --> 00:23:49,722
they made for
the winter dance at school.

502
00:23:49,762 --> 00:23:52,026
I don't count that, no.

503
00:23:52,064 --> 00:23:55,090
But just wait.

504
00:23:55,134 --> 00:23:56,659
When the snow covers everything
in sight

505
00:23:56,702 --> 00:23:58,830
and the Christmas
lights reflect off of it...

506
00:23:58,871 --> 00:24:02,205
in that one, quiet moment,

507
00:24:02,441 --> 00:24:06,776
the world is and
new and perfect.

508
00:24:09,148 --> 00:24:12,015
I like Montana snow better.

509
00:24:12,051 --> 00:24:13,610
Are these the marshmallows
Pops was talking about?

510
00:24:13,652 --> 00:24:16,644
Chloe: Kay let me
and Lexie help.

511
00:24:16,689 --> 00:24:18,214
And then, she taught
us how to knit.

512
00:24:18,457 --> 00:24:19,947
Wow!
You have been busy!

513
00:24:19,992 --> 00:24:21,653
What are you knitting?

514
00:24:21,694 --> 00:24:24,925
Atiny little
Christmas scarf.

515
00:24:24,964 --> 00:24:26,864
Sara: Kay, thank you
for keeping her so busy.

516
00:24:26,899 --> 00:24:29,630
I think I had
more fun than they did.

517
00:24:29,668 --> 00:24:31,762
Did you two get a lot done?

518
00:24:36,542 --> 00:24:39,637
I'm just getting
a feel for the place.

519
00:24:39,678 --> 00:24:41,510
Well, in that case,

520
00:24:41,547 --> 00:24:42,981
I hope you can stay for
lunch in a couple hours.

521
00:24:43,015 --> 00:24:44,847
Mom, can we stay?

522
00:24:44,883 --> 00:24:47,909
Well, just as long as there's no
talking business at the table.

523
00:24:47,953 --> 00:24:50,786
Well, then, we're going to have
to talk about it before lunch.

524
00:24:50,823 --> 00:24:52,086
There's just enough time for me

525
00:24:52,124 --> 00:24:54,525
to go through your
most recent balance sheet.

526
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:56,619
{blowing raspberry)

527
00:24:56,662 --> 00:24:57,925
Oh, can I go visit
the horses while you guys work?

528
00:24:57,963 --> 00:24:58,930
Go ahead.

529
00:24:58,964 --> 00:25:00,090
Can I go too?

530
00:25:00,132 --> 00:25:01,725
Funny.

531
00:25:01,767 --> 00:25:03,929
{Chloe chuckling)

532
00:25:05,904 --> 00:25:08,271
Let's go.

533
00:25:11,210 --> 00:25:13,838
Ranching is actually
a lot more high-tech

534
00:25:13,879 --> 00:25:15,278
than most people think.

535
00:25:15,514 --> 00:25:18,040
With GPS, I can see where every
single head of cattle is

536
00:25:18,083 --> 00:25:19,608
on a screen at one time.

537
00:25:19,651 --> 00:25:21,517
This is not what I expected
your office to look like.

538
00:25:21,553 --> 00:25:25,046
One second.

539
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:27,582
How about now?

540
00:25:27,626 --> 00:25:29,253
Yes.
That's what was missing.

541
00:25:29,294 --> 00:25:30,728
You know, I have
never met anyone

542
00:25:30,763 --> 00:25:32,857
as into Christmas as you.

543
00:25:32,898 --> 00:25:35,299
Making up for lost time.

544
00:25:35,534 --> 00:25:38,868
I think when I left the ranch,
I left Christmas behind, too.

545
00:25:38,904 --> 00:25:40,269
Where did you go?

546
00:25:42,241 --> 00:25:43,265
Law school.

547
00:25:43,308 --> 00:25:45,276
You're a lawyer?

548
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:47,904
Was, yeah. I was pretty good
at it, too.

549
00:25:47,946 --> 00:25:50,313
But itwasn't
what I was looking for.

550
00:25:50,549 --> 00:25:52,210
What were you looking for?

551
00:25:52,251 --> 00:25:54,310
Something different.

552
00:25:54,553 --> 00:25:56,214
I mean, haven't you ever
wanted a change

553
00:25:56,255 --> 00:25:57,950
just to see if that's
where you were meant to be?

554
00:25:57,990 --> 00:25:59,719
Not really.

555
00:25:59,758 --> 00:26:01,692
The reason I'm up
for a promotion

556
00:26:01,727 --> 00:26:04,162
is because I stayed the course,
I rose up through the ranks.

557
00:26:04,196 --> 00:26:06,563
There's something
to be said for stability.

558
00:26:06,598 --> 00:26:09,260
Yes, there is,
and I had that in New York.

559
00:26:09,301 --> 00:26:11,235
But after a few years,

560
00:26:11,270 --> 00:26:14,103
I just had to admit
that I wasn't happy.

561
00:26:14,139 --> 00:26:17,109
I missed everything
single thing about this place,

562
00:26:17,142 --> 00:26:18,837
especially at Christmas.

563
00:26:18,877 --> 00:26:20,743
You missed Christmas
in New York City,

564
00:26:20,779 --> 00:26:22,247
the most Christmassy
place in the world?

565
00:26:22,281 --> 00:26:24,807
ltwasn't home.

566
00:26:26,618 --> 00:26:29,280
Sometimes home is the hardest
place to be at Christmas.

567
00:26:29,321 --> 00:26:32,586
Hmm.

568
00:26:32,624 --> 00:26:35,150
Well, in that case,

569
00:26:35,194 --> 00:26:39,688
I hope that someday you can
bring Christmas home again.

570
00:26:42,167 --> 00:26:44,192
I'll show you our
balance sheets.

571
00:26:53,245 --> 00:26:58,046
Okay, anything on
a green plate is vegetarian.

572
00:26:58,083 --> 00:27:00,177
That is so thoughtful.
Thank you.

573
00:27:00,219 --> 00:27:03,018
Oh, thank Kay -
she put it together.

574
00:27:03,055 --> 00:27:05,683
Amazing in
the kitchen, this one.

575
00:27:05,724 --> 00:27:08,352
Yeah, when Kay's not around,
things aren't quite as gourmet.

576
00:27:08,393 --> 00:27:10,828
I don't know
why I picture ranchers

577
00:27:10,863 --> 00:27:13,264
eating beans out of a tin pot.

578
00:27:13,298 --> 00:27:15,824
What? That is a cliché
from a bad movie.

579
00:27:15,868 --> 00:27:18,200
Son, remind me

580
00:27:18,237 --> 00:27:19,796
what we had for
supper last night?

581
00:27:21,106 --> 00:27:23,200
Beans.

582
00:27:24,643 --> 00:27:26,771
Straight out of the pot.

583
00:27:26,812 --> 00:27:29,907
(all chuckling)

584
00:27:29,948 --> 00:27:32,974
While you picture
ranchers eating beans,

585
00:27:33,018 --> 00:27:37,046
I picture people from LA
eating kale, like all the time.

586
00:27:37,089 --> 00:27:39,751
Well, I guess we both have
certain misconceptions.

587
00:27:41,260 --> 00:27:43,422
Mom, you had kale
chips on the plane.

588
00:27:43,662 --> 00:27:47,292
- Shh...
- (all laughing)

589
00:27:47,332 --> 00:27:50,358
So, Chloe, what do you think
of the ranch so far?

590
00:27:50,402 --> 00:27:53,770
Um, it's pretty cool.

591
00:27:53,805 --> 00:27:56,240
Trust me.
This is high praise.

592
00:27:56,275 --> 00:28:00,439
You are here at
the best time of the year.

593
00:28:00,679 --> 00:28:02,841
Some of the fondest
memories of my life

594
00:28:02,881 --> 00:28:06,010
are from Christmas
on this ranch.

595
00:28:06,051 --> 00:28:07,450
Me, too, Dad.

596
00:28:07,686 --> 00:28:09,313
(chuckling)

597
00:28:09,354 --> 00:28:10,947
In fact, I get just as
excited for Christmas now

598
00:28:10,989 --> 00:28:12,081
as I did when I was a kid.

599
00:28:12,124 --> 00:28:13,785
When I was a kid,

600
00:28:13,825 --> 00:28:16,260
I loved that moment of seeing
the Christmas tree all lit up,

601
00:28:16,295 --> 00:28:19,287
Christmas Eve,
right before Santa came,

602
00:28:19,331 --> 00:28:24,201
and I just wished that feeling
could last forever.

603
00:28:24,236 --> 00:28:27,433
I know exactly how you feel.

604
00:28:29,708 --> 00:28:31,802
What about you, Chloe?

605
00:28:31,843 --> 00:28:33,937
What's your favorite
Christmas memory?

606
00:28:36,248 --> 00:28:37,943
Um...

607
00:28:37,983 --> 00:28:42,079
just..spending time
with family.

608
00:28:44,289 --> 00:28:47,088
That's my favorite part, too.

609
00:28:49,361 --> 00:28:51,728
Travis: My absolutely favorite
thing about Christmas

610
00:28:51,763 --> 00:28:53,356
is actually
happening tonight,

611
00:28:53,398 --> 00:28:55,765
it's the Carson Ranch
Christmas bonfire,

612
00:28:55,801 --> 00:29:00,398
sort of a gigantic campout
with family and friends,

613
00:29:00,439 --> 00:29:04,069
and it's just... joyful.

614
00:29:04,109 --> 00:29:06,134
I hope you and
Chloe will join us.

615
00:29:06,178 --> 00:29:07,441
You better save them

616
00:29:07,479 --> 00:29:08,810
front row seats in
front of the fire.

617
00:29:08,847 --> 00:29:10,406
It's going to be
in the low-20's tonight.

618
00:29:10,449 --> 00:29:12,110
Oh, yeah, that's right.

619
00:29:12,150 --> 00:29:13,515
You guys aren't
equipped for this.

620
00:29:13,752 --> 00:29:15,151
(sighing)

621
00:29:15,187 --> 00:29:17,087
So, Chloe, I don't think
we have much choice.

622
00:29:17,122 --> 00:29:18,817
Either with stay indoors

623
00:29:18,857 --> 00:29:20,791
while I finish my work
and we fly back to LA,

624
00:29:20,826 --> 00:29:22,954
or we go into town and we
get ourselves some new coats.

625
00:29:24,463 --> 00:29:26,158
I vote coats.

626
00:29:26,198 --> 00:29:29,828
Well, the snow's coming down
pretty hard. If you want,

627
00:29:29,868 --> 00:29:32,462
I can give you a lift into town,

628
00:29:32,504 --> 00:29:34,404
Oh, you don't need to do that.

629
00:29:34,439 --> 00:29:37,773
Have-- have you
ever driven in the snow?

630
00:29:37,809 --> 00:29:41,074
We barely drive in the rain.

631
00:29:41,113 --> 00:29:42,877
(all laughing)

632
00:29:46,118 --> 00:29:56,085
I

633
00:30:10,842 --> 00:30:12,435
I don't know about this coat.

634
00:30:12,477 --> 00:30:14,377
Here, try this one.

635
00:30:14,413 --> 00:30:16,006
Ooh.

636
00:30:16,048 --> 00:30:17,982
How does anyone
move around in these?

637
00:30:18,016 --> 00:30:20,280
Ah, you figure it out.

638
00:30:20,319 --> 00:30:22,083
I'm never taking it off.

639
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:23,349
Excellent.

640
00:30:23,388 --> 00:30:24,913
Actually, I like it.

641
00:30:24,956 --> 00:30:27,050
Feels like I'm wrapped in a
thousand fuzzy blankets.

642
00:30:27,092 --> 00:30:29,151
We'll take these.

643
00:30:32,497 --> 00:30:33,862
So, back to the ranch?

644
00:30:33,899 --> 00:30:35,424
Uh, no. We have
one more errand to run.

645
00:30:35,467 --> 00:30:36,457
Merry Christmas.

646
00:30:36,501 --> 00:30:37,866
Oh, merry Christmas.

647
00:30:37,903 --> 00:30:39,029
Merry Christmas.

648
00:30:39,071 --> 00:30:40,197
Merry Christmas.

649
00:30:40,238 --> 00:30:41,899
You can't possibly
know all these people.

650
00:30:41,940 --> 00:30:43,931
Oh, I don't.
Don't know that guy.

651
00:30:43,975 --> 00:30:46,603
Oh. No, wait. I do.
Merry Christmas, Stan!

652
00:30:46,845 --> 00:30:49,314
(chuckling)

653
00:30:49,348 --> 00:30:52,045
All right, load up.
You know what they say -

654
00:30:52,084 --> 00:30:53,074
Cold hands, cold head--

655
00:30:53,118 --> 00:30:54,608
Cold heart?

656
00:30:54,853 --> 00:30:58,050
No. Just put it on or
you'll be super cold.

657
00:30:58,090 --> 00:31:00,616
Here you go.
Merry Christmas.

658
00:31:00,859 --> 00:31:01,951
Oh. Oh, that's a hard pass.

659
00:31:01,993 --> 00:31:03,427
You can't say no. It's a gift.

660
00:31:03,462 --> 00:31:05,521
- Then, thank you.
- You're welcome.

661
00:31:05,564 --> 00:31:06,588
Oh...

662
00:31:06,631 --> 00:31:08,998
Oh my goodness.

663
00:31:09,034 --> 00:31:11,332
Oh. Oh, you're killing me.

664
00:31:11,370 --> 00:31:13,031
I think it's awesome.

665
00:31:13,071 --> 00:31:14,596
Thank you very much
for this hat.

666
00:31:14,639 --> 00:31:16,403
Oh, look what I found.

667
00:31:16,441 --> 00:31:17,602
No way.

668
00:31:17,642 --> 00:31:19,167
Turnaround is fair play.

669
00:31:19,211 --> 00:31:20,372
Adorable.

670
00:31:20,412 --> 00:31:21,345
- It's awful.
- What about me?

671
00:31:21,380 --> 00:31:23,348
- Thank you.
- What about me?

672
00:31:23,382 --> 00:31:24,440
Oh. Take this guy.

673
00:31:24,483 --> 00:31:26,247
Oh, thank you.

674
00:31:26,284 --> 00:31:27,877
Ooh, I actually
look cute.

675
00:31:27,919 --> 00:31:30,388
Travis: You do!
That's disappointing.

676
00:31:30,422 --> 00:31:31,355
(chuckling)

677
00:31:31,390 --> 00:31:33,119
Oh, that's horrifying.

678
00:31:33,158 --> 00:31:34,421
- Truly.
- It's the worst.

679
00:31:34,459 --> 00:31:36,257
Oh, I actually really
like these, though.

680
00:31:36,294 --> 00:31:37,455
Oh, can I get them?

681
00:31:37,496 --> 00:31:38,657
Cool. Yeah, we can get these.

682
00:31:38,897 --> 00:31:40,058
- I'll get you some mittens.
- Thank you.

683
00:31:40,098 --> 00:31:41,190
Sweet.

684
00:31:42,968 --> 00:31:44,129
Thank you.

685
00:31:44,169 --> 00:31:46,160
Thank you.

686
00:31:46,204 --> 00:31:48,104
Slow down!

687
00:31:48,140 --> 00:31:49,608
Does she always
walk so fast?

688
00:31:49,641 --> 00:31:52,008
Yep. There's nothing she
hates more than a stroll.

689
00:31:52,043 --> 00:31:53,533
Not when there's
so much to do.

690
00:31:53,578 --> 00:31:55,342
I've been researching
regenerative soil techniques,

691
00:31:55,380 --> 00:31:57,644
modernization, and there's just
a lot to think about.

692
00:31:57,682 --> 00:31:59,309
You really do care, huh?

693
00:31:59,351 --> 00:32:00,546
I told you I did.

694
00:32:00,585 --> 00:32:02,110
Oh, we have one
more thing to get.

695
00:32:02,154 --> 00:32:03,349
Boots?

696
00:32:03,388 --> 00:32:04,981
Boots.

697
00:32:05,023 --> 00:32:06,149
Boots.

698
00:32:11,263 --> 00:32:13,231
(chattering, cheering)

699
00:32:13,265 --> 00:32:16,633
Let's pass these around.

700
00:32:16,668 --> 00:32:20,127
Oh, Chloe,
this is my mom and dad.

701
00:32:20,172 --> 00:32:21,367
Hi, Chloe.

702
00:32:21,406 --> 00:32:23,135
Hi.
It's great to meet you.

703
00:32:23,175 --> 00:32:24,233
Yeah, you, too.

704
00:32:24,276 --> 00:32:25,505
Let's go roast these.

705
00:32:25,544 --> 00:32:28,241
Have fun.

706
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:30,078
You know, you could make
a lot of extra income

707
00:32:30,115 --> 00:32:32,140
by selling this, right?

708
00:32:32,184 --> 00:32:34,414
That's not what
Christmas is about.

709
00:32:34,453 --> 00:32:37,252
We're not gonna take
money from my friends.

710
00:32:38,690 --> 00:32:40,522
I get it.

711
00:32:40,559 --> 00:32:42,027
What?

712
00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:44,529
Why this is your favorite thing.

713
00:32:44,563 --> 00:32:47,692
Everyone is just out
celebrating.

714
00:32:47,732 --> 00:32:50,531
Nobody's rushing,
nobody's stressed.

715
00:32:50,569 --> 00:32:53,470
It's like everyone pressed
‘pause' for the night.

716
00:32:53,505 --> 00:32:55,530
You can do it, too.

717
00:32:55,574 --> 00:32:57,736
I can't seem
to get out of fast forward.

718
00:32:57,976 --> 00:33:01,139
Give ittime.
You'll figure it out.

719
00:33:01,179 --> 00:33:03,978
I'm don't think
we'll be here long enough.

720
00:33:04,015 --> 00:33:06,507
Hi. Well, it's almost time
for Christmas carols.

721
00:33:06,551 --> 00:33:10,010
So, what is your favorite?

722
00:33:10,055 --> 00:33:11,545
Uh... I don't know.

723
00:33:11,590 --> 00:33:13,080
We already did "Jingle Bells"
with the horse.

724
00:33:13,124 --> 00:33:15,593
So, maybe "Deck the Halls?"

725
00:33:15,627 --> 00:33:18,221
Done.
That would've been my pick.

726
00:33:19,498 --> 00:33:20,659
Travis.

727
00:33:20,699 --> 00:33:22,133
Hey! Oh, hey.

728
00:33:22,167 --> 00:33:23,464
Um, Sara and Chloe Bradley,

729
00:33:23,502 --> 00:33:24,628
this is my
good friend Stephen.

730
00:33:24,669 --> 00:33:26,467
He runs the best
restaurant in Big Fork.

731
00:33:26,505 --> 00:33:27,666
Pleasure, ma'am.

732
00:33:27,706 --> 00:33:31,142
Sara is the financial
advisor from California.

733
00:33:31,176 --> 00:33:34,305
Oh. Well, I could've guessed
you weren't from around here.

734
00:33:34,346 --> 00:33:35,472
How?

735
00:33:35,514 --> 00:33:37,209
Uh...

736
00:33:37,249 --> 00:33:38,444
New duds.

737
00:33:38,483 --> 00:33:40,178
Travis, I can't believe
you let me walk around

738
00:33:40,218 --> 00:33:41,583
with that tag inside
my jacket this whole time!

739
00:33:41,620 --> 00:33:43,679
No, I didn't notice! I swear!
I promise. I promise.

740
00:33:43,722 --> 00:33:45,315
Do you want to go
see the marshmallow roast?

741
00:33:45,357 --> 00:33:47,155
I would love to.

742
00:33:47,192 --> 00:33:48,250
Nice to meet you.

743
00:33:48,293 --> 00:33:49,260
Stephen: Likewise.

744
00:33:54,266 --> 00:33:55,791
Haven't seen
that look in your eye

745
00:33:56,034 --> 00:33:57,160
since you moved back from NYC.

746
00:33:57,202 --> 00:33:58,260
Oh, stop.

747
00:33:58,303 --> 00:34:00,533
I'm just saying,
it's nice to see.

748
00:34:11,216 --> 00:34:13,048
(sighing)

749
00:34:13,084 --> 00:34:15,416
This is perfect.

750
00:34:15,453 --> 00:34:16,511
It sure is.

751
