00:36:00,225 --> 00:36:02,159
Hey, Chloe.
I like your boots.

783
00:36:02,193 --> 00:36:04,719
Thank you. They're new.

784
00:36:04,763 --> 00:36:07,528
Would you girls like to
help me with the egg nog?

785
00:36:07,565 --> 00:36:08,657
- Yes!
- Sure!

786
00:36:08,700 --> 00:36:10,498
Okay, first, though,
we need some eggs.

787
00:36:11,836 --> 00:36:13,429
Uh, where you going?

788
00:36:13,471 --> 00:36:14,870
Kitchen's that way.

789
00:36:14,906 --> 00:36:17,170
Yeah, but the eggs
are back there.

790
00:36:17,208 --> 00:36:19,905
Oh, I don't think
I could do that.

791
00:36:19,944 --> 00:36:21,503
You were great with the horses.

792
00:36:21,546 --> 00:36:24,345
The chickens are
even easier. Come on.

793
00:36:24,382 --> 00:36:26,646
Sara: Have fun.

794
00:36:26,685 --> 00:36:28,779
{Kay chuckling)

795
00:36:28,820 --> 00:36:31,414
I'm just gonna have
a look around the ranch.

796
00:36:33,258 --> 00:36:37,889
(lowing)

797
00:36:37,929 --> 00:36:42,833
(lowing)

798
00:36:48,606 --> 00:36:50,836
(chuckling)

799
00:36:50,875 --> 00:36:52,809
-Woman: Hey.
- Man: How you doing?

800
00:36:52,844 --> 00:36:54,209
Hi.

801
00:36:54,245 --> 00:36:56,577
(chattering)

802
00:37:13,264 --> 00:37:15,460
Wow,
this place is coming along.

803
00:37:15,500 --> 00:37:17,867
Yeah. Only four days
till Christmas Eve.

804
00:37:19,404 --> 00:37:20,496
Come on!

805
00:37:20,538 --> 00:37:23,508
Hey!
Snowball fights outside only.

806
00:37:23,541 --> 00:37:24,804
And no sneak attacks.

807
00:37:24,843 --> 00:37:26,470
Sorry, Dad.
Come on, guys.

808
00:37:26,511 --> 00:37:28,001
Chloe: Hey!

809
00:37:28,246 --> 00:37:31,011
Sorry about that, ma'am.
Kids are on break.

810
00:37:31,249 --> 00:37:32,944
Oh, J.T. Ryan -
head ranch hand.

811
00:37:32,984 --> 00:37:34,816
Sara Bradley.
Nice to meet you.

812
00:37:34,853 --> 00:37:38,448
I better go give
Teddy some backup.

813
00:37:38,490 --> 00:37:41,425
Would you do me a favor and
help me unbox these plates?

814
00:37:41,459 --> 00:37:42,824
Sure.

815
00:37:42,861 --> 00:37:45,592
It's amazing to see the whole
town enjoying your ranch.

816
00:37:45,630 --> 00:37:47,758
That's what
Christmas is all about.

817
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,768
I can see that.

818
00:37:51,903 --> 00:37:53,393
These are beautiful.

819
00:37:53,438 --> 00:37:55,338
Thank you.
Some of them were my mom's,

820
00:37:55,373 --> 00:37:56,898
passed down from
three generations before that.

821
00:37:56,941 --> 00:37:58,466
I bet she'd be proud

822
00:37:58,510 --> 00:37:59,875
to know that you're
keeping up the tradition.

823
00:37:59,911 --> 00:38:02,812
Yeah. You know,
that's what I missed

824
00:38:02,847 --> 00:38:04,440
when I was in New York.

825
00:38:04,482 --> 00:38:06,382
It's the things that make
Christmas personal

826
00:38:06,417 --> 00:38:08,476
are the things that you
look forward to the most.

827
00:38:08,520 --> 00:38:09,646
You know?

828
00:38:09,687 --> 00:38:11,781
For me and Chloe,

829
00:38:11,823 --> 00:38:13,882
Christmas just became
something to get through

830
00:38:13,925 --> 00:38:15,916
instead of something
to celebrate.

831
00:38:15,960 --> 00:38:19,487
Have you ever spoken to her
about how things used to be?

832
00:38:19,531 --> 00:38:23,468
I've tried.
It just gets her upset.

833
00:38:23,501 --> 00:38:25,333
I'm sorry.

834
00:38:25,370 --> 00:38:26,531
That's none of my business.

835
00:38:26,571 --> 00:38:28,061
I just know how healing
it was for me

836
00:38:28,306 --> 00:38:30,832
to keep my mother's
traditions alive,

837
00:38:30,875 --> 00:38:32,900
especially not being able to
get back when she was sick...

838
00:38:32,944 --> 00:38:37,040
and then everything
happened so... quickly

839
00:38:37,081 --> 00:38:38,913
I wasn't ready.

840
00:38:38,950 --> 00:38:40,543
I don't think anybody is.

841
00:38:40,585 --> 00:38:42,815
Your whole life
changes in an instant.

842
00:38:42,854 --> 00:38:44,982
That's true.

843
00:38:45,023 --> 00:38:48,857
And the way my parents
loved each other, I mean,

844
00:38:48,893 --> 00:38:52,523
that's how I pictured Christmas
was gonna be with family.

845
00:38:52,564 --> 00:38:54,760
I think you'll be
a wonderful father someday.

846
00:38:54,799 --> 00:38:57,097
You connect so easily to kids.

847
00:38:58,336 --> 00:38:59,804
Thank you.

848
00:39:04,509 --> 00:39:07,342
And Chloe makes it easy.
She's a great kid.

849
00:39:07,378 --> 00:39:10,837
She is lighter here,
more connected.

850
00:39:10,882 --> 00:39:13,783
That's what's great about life
here is connecting with people,

851
00:39:13,818 --> 00:39:16,947
you know,
sitting together, talking.

852
00:39:16,988 --> 00:39:18,456
We take the time,

853
00:39:18,489 --> 00:39:21,049
and enjoy the journey
as much as the destination.

854
00:39:21,092 --> 00:39:22,617
And I'm always too busy

855
00:39:22,660 --> 00:39:24,992
finding my fastest way
to the destination.

856
00:39:25,029 --> 00:39:26,929
You are working
hard to provide

857
00:39:26,965 --> 00:39:29,991
a great life for Chloe,
and you're doing a great job.

858
00:39:30,034 --> 00:39:32,662
Yeah. There's nothing
more important to me.

859
00:39:32,704 --> 00:39:35,401
She needs to know
we're going to be okay.

860
00:39:35,440 --> 00:39:38,501
She's lucky to
have a mom like you.

861
00:39:38,543 --> 00:39:41,376
{footsteps approaching)

862
00:39:41,412 --> 00:39:42,937
(chuckling)

863
00:39:42,981 --> 00:39:44,915
Teddy turned on me.

864
00:39:44,949 --> 00:39:46,781
(chuckling)

865
00:39:46,818 --> 00:39:49,583
Oh, I'll be back after the crew
and I feed the stock.

866
00:39:49,621 --> 00:39:51,953
Let me know if
you need anything.

867
00:39:51,990 --> 00:39:53,048
Will do.

868
00:39:53,091 --> 00:39:54,456
(chuckling)

869
00:39:54,492 --> 00:39:55,982
He's nice.

870
00:39:56,027 --> 00:39:57,995
Yeah,
he's like a brother to me.

871
00:39:58,029 --> 00:40:00,999
His dad worked here,
too, back in the day.

872
00:40:01,032 --> 00:40:04,696
Alot of our ranch hands are
second, even third generation.

873
00:40:04,736 --> 00:40:06,670
I can see why Peter's
recommendations

874
00:40:06,704 --> 00:40:08,069
weren't going to work.

875
00:40:08,106 --> 00:40:10,598
I'm glad you understand.

876
00:40:10,642 --> 00:40:13,577
I do.

877
00:40:20,485 --> 00:40:22,749
- (bell ringing)
- (cows lowing)

878
00:40:22,787 --> 00:40:24,585
Oh. Must be time to go.

879
00:40:24,622 --> 00:40:25,680
Where?

880
00:40:25,723 --> 00:40:27,088
Back to the house.

881
00:40:27,125 --> 00:40:30,527
First rule of ranch life,
never ignore the chow bell.

882
00:40:32,864 --> 00:40:36,494
(chuckling)

883
00:40:36,534 --> 00:40:38,628
Hey. We heard the bell.
What's cooking?

884
00:40:38,670 --> 00:40:42,698
Presenting Chloe
and Lexie's secret--

885
00:40:42,740 --> 00:40:43,707
Both: Super secret.

886
00:40:43,741 --> 00:40:47,769
--Super secret recipe egg nog.

887
00:40:47,812 --> 00:40:49,644
There you go.

888
00:40:49,681 --> 00:40:51,513
Thank you.

889
00:40:53,217 --> 00:40:54,981
Thank you.

890
00:40:55,019 --> 00:40:58,580
Oh, look, I puta cinnamon
stick in, like Dad used to.

891
00:40:58,623 --> 00:41:00,182
You remember that?

892
00:41:00,224 --> 00:41:03,125
I remember everything.

893
00:41:03,161 --> 00:41:04,959
{phone ringing)

894
00:41:04,996 --> 00:41:06,987
Oh. Excuse me. Here.

895
00:41:07,031 --> 00:41:08,521
Sure.

896
00:41:08,566 --> 00:41:09,727
I get some, too.

897
00:41:09,767 --> 00:41:10,928
Fair enough.

898
00:41:10,969 --> 00:41:13,563
(all laughing)

899
00:41:15,006 --> 00:41:16,565
I know, Peter.

900
00:41:16,607 --> 00:41:18,132
But it's different
once you see it in person.

901
00:41:18,176 --> 00:41:20,577
There are just a lot of
moving parts to consider.

902
00:41:20,611 --> 00:41:22,773
Well, if you can't come up with
an alternate solution,

903
00:41:22,814 --> 00:41:24,782
you need to help
him do what he has to do.

904
00:41:24,816 --> 00:41:28,946
Did you send me here to try to
talk him into laying people off?

905
00:41:28,987 --> 00:41:31,217
Well, of course not.
I sent you there

906
00:41:31,255 --> 00:41:32,950
because we're trying to help
one of our oldest clients

907
00:41:32,991 --> 00:41:34,049
hang onto his legacy.

908
00:41:34,092 --> 00:41:36,561
But you only got
three more left, Sara.

909
00:41:36,594 --> 00:41:37,993
At some point,

910
00:41:38,029 --> 00:41:39,895
you're going to have to tell
them the same thing I did.

911
00:41:39,931 --> 00:41:42,662
I still have time. Bye.

912
00:41:42,700 --> 00:41:45,226
Everything okay?

913
00:41:45,269 --> 00:41:46,759
It will be.

914
00:41:46,804 --> 00:41:50,104
I know there's a lot
riding on all this for everyone.

915
00:41:50,141 --> 00:41:52,940
Well, we appreciate
you trying to find

916
00:41:52,977 --> 00:41:54,809
a different way to
make the loan happen.

917
00:41:54,846 --> 00:41:56,780
Yeah, I'm doing my best.

918
00:41:56,814 --> 00:41:59,146
It would be a lot easier
if I didn't care so much...

919
00:42:01,085 --> 00:42:05,989
...about the ranch, and your
family, and the traditions.

920
00:42:06,024 --> 00:42:07,890
I didn't expect that.

921
00:42:07,925 --> 00:42:11,259
I didn't expect that either.

922
00:42:11,295 --> 00:42:13,593
I've got an idea.

923
00:42:13,631 --> 00:42:14,962
What?

924
00:42:14,999 --> 00:42:17,195
Nothing clears
the head like a long ride,

925
00:42:17,235 --> 00:42:19,727
and at Christmas time,
it's even better.

926
00:42:19,771 --> 00:42:21,068
You ever been on a horse?

927
00:42:21,105 --> 00:42:23,164
Does sitting on a pony

928
00:42:23,207 --> 00:42:26,006
walking around in a circle
when you're five count?

929
00:42:26,044 --> 00:42:27,876
No. No, it doesn't.
But don't worry.

930
00:42:27,912 --> 00:42:29,607
welll find the
right horse for you.

931
00:42:29,647 --> 00:42:30,773
It's always good to match

932
00:42:30,815 --> 00:42:32,874
a rider's personality
with a horse.

933
00:42:32,917 --> 00:42:36,615
Sara, this is Liberty.

934
00:42:36,654 --> 00:42:40,215
Smartas a whip,
fiercely loyal

935
00:42:40,258 --> 00:42:42,886
and has a heart of gold.

936
00:42:50,201 --> 00:42:51,327
Hello.

937
00:42:56,607 --> 00:42:59,338
Sara: Do I really
have to wear this thing?

938
00:42:59,577 --> 00:43:02,842
Yes. Safety first.
Now, come on. I'll leg you up.

939
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:04,109
You'll what me up?

940
00:43:04,148 --> 00:43:06,981
You use my hands as a stool,
I give you a boost,

941
00:43:07,018 --> 00:43:08,952
then you throw your other leg
over the back of the horse.

942
00:43:08,986 --> 00:43:11,353
Don't worry about it.
I'll be right here.

943
00:43:11,589 --> 00:43:12,579
- Okay.
- Okay.

944
00:43:12,623 --> 00:43:13,784
- Okay.
- All right?

945
00:43:16,060 --> 00:43:17,221
Yeah.

946
00:43:17,261 --> 00:43:19,730
No, wait. Okay.
Okay, okay.

947
00:43:19,764 --> 00:43:21,323
- I'm right here.
- All right.

948
00:43:21,365 --> 00:43:23,265
You want to try that again?

949
00:43:23,301 --> 00:43:24,666
Yeah. Yeah.
I don't give up so easily.

950
00:43:24,702 --> 00:43:25,897
Okay.

951
00:43:25,937 --> 00:43:27,098
Okay.

952
00:43:27,138 --> 00:43:28,697
Ready?

953
00:43:28,739 --> 00:43:29,968
- Whoo!
- Perfect!

954
00:43:30,007 --> 00:43:31,236
- 1 did it.
- Great job.

955
00:43:31,275 --> 00:43:32,242
- Okay.
- Great job! Oh!

956
00:43:32,276 --> 00:43:33,744
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

957
00:43:33,778 --> 00:43:35,246
You just-- you squeezed
your legs together a little.

958
00:43:35,279 --> 00:43:37,111
- To her, that means "go."
- Okay.

959
00:43:37,148 --> 00:43:38,912
Now, just use the reins, right?

960
00:43:38,950 --> 00:43:41,078
Right, left -
it's like driving a car.

961
00:43:41,119 --> 00:43:42,382
All right. Oh, yeah.
I got this.

962
00:43:42,620 --> 00:43:43,917
- Okay.
- Sara: I got it.

963
00:43:43,955 --> 00:43:46,322
You're doing great.

964
00:43:48,759 --> 00:43:50,249
{clicking tongue)

965
00:43:50,294 --> 00:43:52,854
(horse whinnying)

966
00:44:01,139 --> 00:44:04,404
{sighing contentedly)
This is great.

967
00:44:04,642 --> 00:44:06,132
You're a natural.

968
00:44:06,177 --> 00:44:08,669
Oh, I didn't say go!
I didn't do the leg thing!

969
00:44:08,713 --> 00:44:10,306
Don't worry. You're going
in the right direction.

970
00:44:10,348 --> 00:44:11,406
I got your back.

971
00:44:17,788 --> 00:44:22,089
I

972
00:44:23,294 --> 00:44:24,261
That was amazing.

973
00:44:24,295 --> 00:44:25,262
It was fun, right?

974
00:44:25,296 --> 00:44:26,286
Yeah.

975
00:44:26,330 --> 00:44:27,320
You're a natural.

976
00:44:27,365 --> 00:44:28,696
Thank you.

977
00:44:28,733 --> 00:44:29,894
Thanks, Luke.

978
00:44:33,738 --> 00:44:36,105
Chloe: Mom!
I've been taking photos.

979
00:44:36,140 --> 00:44:38,302
You know how to ride a horse?

980
00:44:38,342 --> 00:44:42,006
It was more like walking a
horse, but I suppose, yes.

981
00:44:42,046 --> 00:44:44,037
You want to learn how?

982
00:44:44,081 --> 00:44:46,345
So, we could go riding
together someday?

983
00:44:46,384 --> 00:44:47,909
I would love that.

984
00:44:50,955 --> 00:44:53,890
Hey, Neil.
Hey, kids. Merry Christmas.

985
00:44:53,925 --> 00:44:57,259
Merry Christmas,
and thanks again.

986
00:44:57,295 --> 00:44:58,922
Qur pleasure.

987
00:45:00,831 --> 00:45:02,390
Oh, that's the Hayes family.

988
00:45:02,433 --> 00:45:04,993
They get their tree
from us every year.

989
00:45:05,036 --> 00:45:07,403
Hmm. I'll see
you guys at the house.

990
00:45:07,438 --> 00:45:09,031
- See ya, sweetie.
- Okay.

991
00:45:09,073 --> 00:45:10,837
You didn't mention you were
running a Christmas tree lot.

992
00:45:10,875 --> 00:45:12,240
Well, we aren't.

993
00:45:12,276 --> 00:45:13,971
But I invite people to get
their trees from us every year.

994
00:45:14,011 --> 00:45:15,172
And you don't charge for that.

995
00:45:15,213 --> 00:45:16,806
Well, no. That'd be
like me charging you

996
00:45:16,847 --> 00:45:18,747
for riding lessons.

997
00:45:18,783 --> 00:45:21,480
I mean, I realize it's
not a huge income stream,

998
00:45:21,719 --> 00:45:23,153
but every little bit helps.

999
00:45:23,187 --> 00:45:24,450
Well, tell you what,

1000
00:45:24,488 --> 00:45:25,922
if you come up with us
to get our tree tonight,

1001
00:45:25,957 --> 00:45:28,085
I will charge you for the honor.

1002
00:45:28,125 --> 00:45:30,389
You're joking, but you're
actually onto something.

1003
00:45:30,428 --> 00:45:32,328
Am I?

1004
00:45:32,363 --> 00:45:35,355
So, why do you wait so long
to cut down your tree?

1005
00:45:35,399 --> 00:45:37,231
Well, my dad couldn't take any
time off work

1006
00:45:37,268 --> 00:45:38,827
until a couple days
before Christmas,

1007
00:45:38,869 --> 00:45:40,837
so we'd save up all the
decorating until then.

1008
00:45:40,871 --> 00:45:43,806
and I guess it just
became a tradition.

1009
00:45:43,841 --> 00:45:47,141
Seems like everything around
here becomes a tradition.

1010
00:45:47,178 --> 00:45:49,203
Well, when you find
something special,

1011
00:45:49,247 --> 00:45:51,807
you try to keep it around.

1012
00:45:56,787 --> 00:45:58,915
(Sara exhaling deeply)

1013
00:45:58,956 --> 00:46:01,152
Oh, it's beautiful out here.

1014
00:46:01,192 --> 00:46:04,218
I mean, it's like a
show globe come to life.

1015
00:46:04,262 --> 00:46:06,924
It's like what everyone thinks
Christmas should look like.

1016
00:46:06,964 --> 00:46:08,989
Merry Christmas!

1017
00:46:09,033 --> 00:46:11,502
How can you do this every year
without losing all your trees?

1018
00:46:11,535 --> 00:46:14,129
Well, we plant two for every
one that someone takes.

1019
00:46:14,171 --> 00:46:16,071
I mean, that's what ranching is,
its cyclical,

1020
00:46:16,107 --> 00:46:17,404
everything has
atime and a place,

1021
00:46:17,441 --> 00:46:19,535
and everything we do now
matters for the future.

1022
00:46:19,777 --> 00:46:21,211
Come on, come on.
Less talking, more looking

1023
00:46:21,245 --> 00:46:22,406
Okay.

1024
00:46:28,853 --> 00:46:31,015
(chuckling)

1025
00:46:31,055 --> 00:46:33,149
How ‘bout that one?

1026
00:46:33,190 --> 00:46:35,420
Ehh. It's a good
Charlie Brown Christmas tree.

1027
00:46:35,459 --> 00:46:37,427
Or how ‘bout that one?

1028
00:46:37,461 --> 00:46:41,989
welll find
one for you.

1029
00:46:42,033 --> 00:46:43,364
This is the one.

1030
00:46:43,401 --> 00:46:45,426
That's a great one.
You've got a good eye.

1031
00:46:47,571 --> 00:46:49,096
Here you go.

1032
00:46:49,140 --> 00:46:50,539
You want me to do it?

1033
00:46:50,574 --> 00:46:53,043
It's all a part of the Christmas
in Montana experience, yeah.

1034
00:46:55,346 --> 00:46:57,246
I suppose it is.

1035
00:46:57,281 --> 00:46:58,214
Okay.

1036
00:46:58,249 --> 00:46:59,341
Come on, Mom, let's doit.

1037
00:46:59,383 --> 00:47:02,080
