01:01:19,876 --> 01:01:22,277
Well, unless Sara has some
other recommendations,

1296
01:01:22,312 --> 01:01:24,679
this is the only answer.

1297
01:01:24,714 --> 01:01:26,773
Are you sure?

1298
01:01:26,816 --> 01:01:29,877
No, and I hate to
part of our land,

1299
01:01:29,920 --> 01:01:32,252
but it's better than
losing the people we love.

1300
01:01:35,926 --> 01:01:38,156
Both: I need to talk to you.

1301
01:01:38,195 --> 01:01:40,425
I'll leave you two. Sara.

1302
01:01:40,463 --> 01:01:43,398
Please, let me go first.

1303
01:01:45,802 --> 01:01:47,429
I'm gonna sell
two thousand acres.

1304
01:01:47,470 --> 01:01:50,735
What? But that's ten percent
of your property.

1305
01:01:50,774 --> 01:01:53,368
I know, but this way,
we won't need the loan at all.

1306
01:01:53,410 --> 01:01:55,037
Maybe not this year,
but what about the future?

1307
01:01:55,078 --> 01:01:56,842
What if there's another drought?

1308
01:01:56,880 --> 01:01:58,939
This is what
we have to do now.

1309
01:01:58,982 --> 01:02:02,316
But if you listen to what I have
to say, you might never have to.

1310
01:02:02,352 --> 01:02:04,980
Okay.
What are you talking about?

1311
01:02:05,021 --> 01:02:06,887
It finally hit me.

1312
01:02:06,923 --> 01:02:10,018
This was never going to work
if we focus on cutting costs.

1313
01:02:10,060 --> 01:02:13,030
It's about adding profitability
year in and year out

1314
01:02:13,063 --> 01:02:15,760
by monetizing everything you're
already doing for Christmas.

1315
01:02:15,799 --> 01:02:17,062
Oh, we already
talked about this.

1316
01:02:17,100 --> 01:02:18,761
That is not what
this ranch is about.

1317
01:02:18,802 --> 01:02:20,361
I'm not gonna charge
my family and friends.

1318
01:02:20,403 --> 01:02:21,837
No, you don't need to.

1319
01:02:21,871 --> 01:02:23,862
This is about the people
who would travel here

1320
01:02:23,907 --> 01:02:26,376
to find that classic,

1321
01:02:26,409 --> 01:02:28,969
old-fashioned,
Christmas they're longing for.

1322
01:02:29,012 --> 01:02:30,241
Just-just look at
the proposal, okay?

1323
01:02:30,280 --> 01:02:31,805
- Okay.
- Just let me show it to you.

1324
01:02:31,848 --> 01:02:32,974
All right.

1325
01:02:39,789 --> 01:02:44,522
("We Wish You a
Merry Christmas" playing)

1326
01:02:51,868 --> 01:02:56,806
I

1327
01:02:59,109 --> 01:03:01,908
What do you think?

1328
01:03:01,945 --> 01:03:03,413
And you're sure
there's a market for this?

1329
01:03:03,446 --> 01:03:06,040
I was up all night
doing the research.

1330
01:03:06,082 --> 01:03:08,813
There are already a couple of
ranches upstate doing this.

1331
01:03:10,987 --> 01:03:14,048
And look at what they
charge per week.

1332
01:03:14,090 --> 01:03:15,421
Wow!

1333
01:03:15,458 --> 01:03:18,428
Now you see why I got
so excited about the idea.

1334
01:03:20,063 --> 01:03:22,157
But who'd run it, though?

1335
01:03:22,198 --> 01:03:24,030
I mean, Pops and I
still have to run the ranch.

1336
01:03:24,067 --> 01:03:25,125
Well, you'd have to
hire a manager

1337
01:03:25,168 --> 01:03:27,933
and that is all
laid out in this budget.

1338
01:03:27,971 --> 01:03:29,439
I also worked out
a loan structure

1339
01:03:29,472 --> 01:03:32,305
so that you could get the
initial funding to renovate.

1340
01:03:34,511 --> 01:03:38,243
Travis,
"Christmas at Carson Ranch"

1341
01:03:38,281 --> 01:03:41,046
is about giving people
something they're missing -

1342
01:03:41,084 --> 01:03:43,075
a connection to Christmas,

1343
01:03:43,119 --> 01:03:45,213
to family, to themselves.

1344
01:03:45,255 --> 01:03:48,555
I know that's what it
did for me and Chloe

1345
01:03:48,591 --> 01:03:51,060
and we will always be grateful.

1346
01:03:54,164 --> 01:03:57,031
I'm so glad we came here.

1347
01:03:57,067 --> 01:04:00,367
I am, too.

1348
01:04:00,403 --> 01:04:02,497
So, what do you think?

1349
01:04:02,539 --> 01:04:05,531
Do you want to move forward?

1350
01:04:05,575 --> 01:04:08,977
Definitely.

1351
01:04:09,012 --> 01:04:13,006
I

1352
01:04:25,895 --> 01:04:28,023
Everybody ready?

1353
01:04:28,064 --> 01:04:29,498
Uh, for what?

1354
01:04:29,532 --> 01:04:31,557
We still have to
decorate the gingerbread houses

1355
01:04:31,601 --> 01:04:33,296
for the dessert table,
of course.

1356
01:04:33,336 --> 01:04:36,567
Yeah, I'm not sure
if it's the right time.

1357
01:04:36,606 --> 01:04:38,074
It's the perfect time.

1358
01:04:38,108 --> 01:04:39,542
I mean, we all
need to do something

1359
01:04:39,576 --> 01:04:41,237
while we're waiting, right?

1360
01:04:41,277 --> 01:04:43,405
Can Lexie come, too?

1361
01:04:43,446 --> 01:04:45,608
Of course.
The more the merrier.

1362
01:04:45,648 --> 01:04:48,276
It'll help the time go faster.

1363
01:04:48,318 --> 01:04:50,218
Okay.

1364
01:04:50,253 --> 01:04:53,188
Hey, let's get started.

1365
01:04:57,060 --> 01:05:00,052
Sara:
So, what do you think?

1366
01:05:00,096 --> 01:05:01,257
Well, its gonna
be fantastic.

1367
01:05:01,297 --> 01:05:02,890
I just hope it
isn't the only version

1368
01:05:02,932 --> 01:05:04,331
of the Christmas
ranch we get to see.

1369
01:05:04,367 --> 01:05:05,892
I'm sure it's fine.

1370
01:05:05,935 --> 01:05:08,131
It's the 23rd.

1371
01:05:08,171 --> 01:05:09,434
I mean, that's the
day of our deadline.

1372
01:05:09,472 --> 01:05:11,065
Shouldn't we have heard
something by now?

1373
01:05:11,107 --> 01:05:13,235
Well, the underwriters have
until end of business today.

1374
01:05:13,276 --> 01:05:16,143
I suppose, technically, they
have as long as they want.

1375
01:05:16,179 --> 01:05:18,011
Wait, they can
extend the deadline?

1376
01:05:18,047 --> 01:05:22,678
I guess if they
can't decide by today, yes.

1377
01:05:24,587 --> 01:05:27,249
So, we can stay for Christmas?

1378
01:05:27,290 --> 01:05:29,224
I mean, we can't leave

1379
01:05:29,259 --> 01:05:30,988
until we know for sure
about the loan, right?

1380
01:05:31,027 --> 01:05:32,961
Chloe, they have
their own traditions.

1381
01:05:32,996 --> 01:05:34,122
We don't want to impose.

1382
01:05:34,164 --> 01:05:36,258
Pops: You think you'd impose?

1383
01:05:36,299 --> 01:05:37,528
Part of our tradition

1384
01:05:37,567 --> 01:05:40,662
is having people we care
about here with us -

1385
01:05:40,703 --> 01:05:45,106
family and friends
old and new, and that's you.

1386
01:05:45,141 --> 01:05:47,508
It really wouldn't
be the same without you.

1387
01:05:53,116 --> 01:05:57,110
In that case there's
no place we'd rather be.

1388
01:05:57,153 --> 01:06:00,555
I guess we'll
postpone our flights.

1389
01:06:00,590 --> 01:06:01,989
Great.

1390
01:06:04,093 --> 01:06:17,598
I

1391
01:06:19,509 --> 01:06:21,170
(sighing)

1392
01:06:21,211 --> 01:06:23,236
{phone ringing)

1393
01:06:23,279 --> 01:06:25,111
Hello?

1394
01:06:25,148 --> 01:06:29,016
Hi. Okay.

1395
01:06:29,052 --> 01:06:31,487
Okay.

1396
01:06:33,323 --> 01:06:35,621
Okay. Thank you.
I'll tell them.

1397
01:06:39,562 --> 01:06:40,757
(sighing)

1398
01:06:42,432 --> 01:06:43,763
The Carson Christmas Ranch...

1399
01:06:44,000 --> 01:06:46,162
is officially in business!

1400
01:06:46,202 --> 01:06:47,169
Yes!

1401
01:06:47,203 --> 01:06:48,329
We got the loan?

1402
01:06:48,371 --> 01:06:50,703
- You got the loan!
- We got the loan! Oh!

1403
01:06:50,740 --> 01:06:52,003
You did it!

1404
01:06:52,041 --> 01:06:53,099
No, we did it!

1405
01:06:53,142 --> 01:06:54,268
We should celebrate.

1406
01:06:54,310 --> 01:06:55,641
What did you have in mind?

1407
01:06:55,678 --> 01:06:58,147
Well, actually,
Stephen is having a little,

1408
01:06:58,181 --> 01:06:59,512
you know, party at his
restaurant,

1409
01:06:59,549 --> 01:07:02,246
kind of a
Christmas Eve-Eve tradition.

1410
01:07:02,285 --> 01:07:04,014
Maybe-- maybe we should go.

1411
01:07:04,053 --> 01:07:08,217
Uh, Chloe's welcome
too, of course. You all are.

1412
01:07:08,258 --> 01:07:09,623
What do you think, Chloe?

1413
01:07:09,659 --> 01:07:12,128
Mom, Lexie invited me

1414
01:07:12,161 --> 01:07:14,493
to go Christmas caroling with
her friends from school.

1415
01:07:14,531 --> 01:07:17,228
Her parents are chaperoning us.

1416
01:07:17,267 --> 01:07:18,632
That sounds like fun.

1417
01:07:18,668 --> 01:07:20,227
So, it's okay if I go?

1418
01:07:20,270 --> 01:07:22,398
Of course you can.

1419
01:07:22,438 --> 01:07:26,397
Kay and I could drop Chloe off
and then Kay would be at the B&B

1420
01:07:26,442 --> 01:07:28,501
to watch her when
she came back. Okay?

1421
01:07:28,545 --> 01:07:29,740
Mm-hmm.

1422
01:07:29,779 --> 01:07:32,077
Okay.

1423
01:07:32,115 --> 01:07:34,550
Then, that leaves
us the two of us.

1424
01:07:34,584 --> 01:07:36,416
I guess so.

1425
01:07:42,525 --> 01:07:45,358
Well, I'm so thrilled
for you, Travis.

1426
01:07:45,395 --> 01:07:46,726
Yeah?
About the Christmas Ranch?

1427
01:07:46,763 --> 01:07:50,757
Yes, but that's not
what I was talking about.

1428
01:07:52,535 --> 01:07:55,527
By the way, um...

1429
01:07:55,572 --> 01:07:58,473
I'm really glad you've
been coming around more often.

1430
01:07:58,508 --> 01:08:02,138
Oh. Because of all
the food that I bring?

1431
01:08:02,178 --> 01:08:06,376
Yes... but that's not what
I'm talking about.

1432
01:08:07,417 --> 01:08:09,317
Oh...
(chuckling)

1433
01:08:12,221 --> 01:08:23,599
I

1434
01:08:31,140 --> 01:08:32,471
You look beautiful.

1435
01:08:32,508 --> 01:08:34,476
You look great, too.

1436
01:08:34,510 --> 01:08:36,501
Thank you.

1437
01:08:36,546 --> 01:08:38,537
But I thought you'd
be wearing a bolo tie.

1438
01:08:38,581 --> 01:08:43,542
A bolo? No. I only wear those
on days that end in "never."

1439
01:08:51,194 --> 01:08:53,526
Big Fork really knows
how to celebrate Christmas.

1440
01:08:53,563 --> 01:08:55,190
That's how we do
things around here -

1441
01:08:55,231 --> 01:08:56,494
go big or go home.

1442
01:08:56,532 --> 01:08:58,796
I don't know how anyone
leaves this place.

1443
01:08:58,835 --> 01:09:00,530
Oh, they do.

1444
01:09:00,570 --> 01:09:01,765
But if they have any
Montana is in their soul,

1445
01:09:01,804 --> 01:09:03,898
they always
find their way back.

1446
01:09:04,140 --> 01:09:06,165
Like you did from New York?

1447
01:09:06,209 --> 01:09:10,203
Yeah. Yeah, I didn't realize how
good I had it until I left.

1448
01:09:10,246 --> 01:09:12,840
Sometimes you don't where you
belong until you get there

1449
01:09:12,882 --> 01:09:14,748
and then it all
becomes so clear.

1450
01:09:14,784 --> 01:09:17,583
Exactly.

1451
01:09:19,389 --> 01:09:21,824
Real glad to see you two.

1452
01:09:21,858 --> 01:09:23,553
Now, order whatever you like.

1453
01:09:23,593 --> 01:09:25,288
It's on the house.

1454
01:09:25,328 --> 01:09:28,263
Thank you.

1455
01:09:28,297 --> 01:09:29,822
(sighing)

1456
01:09:29,866 --> 01:09:32,665
(clearing throat)

1457
01:09:36,172 --> 01:09:38,732
Oh.

1458
01:09:38,775 --> 01:09:42,234
It helps to be
good friends with the chef.

1459
01:09:44,347 --> 01:09:49,251
Roasted tofu with quinoa,
peaches and fennel. Wow.

1460
01:09:49,285 --> 01:09:52,550
Is that a good wow or, like...
{unenthusiastically) "Wow."

1461
01:09:52,588 --> 01:09:56,855
That's a great "wow."
Thank you for doing that for me.

1462
01:09:56,893 --> 01:09:59,225
Well, you jumped into the
Montana life with both feet.

1463
01:09:59,262 --> 01:10:00,923
I figured the least I could do

1464
01:10:00,963 --> 01:10:03,432
is try a little bit
of California.

1465
01:10:07,603 --> 01:10:09,901
What?

1466
01:10:09,939 --> 01:10:12,704
If you had asked me a month ago

1467
01:10:12,742 --> 01:10:15,211
where I would be
on Christmas Eve-Eve,

1468
01:10:15,244 --> 01:10:16,837
my answer definitely would not
have been

1469
01:10:16,879 --> 01:10:18,711
"having a candlelight
vegetarian dinner

1470
01:10:18,748 --> 01:10:22,776
"with a cattle rancher
from Big Fork, Montana."

1471
01:10:22,819 --> 01:10:26,414
Really? 'Cause that's what my
answer would have been.

1472
01:10:30,960 --> 01:10:34,863
{both laughing)

1473
01:10:36,532 --> 01:10:40,696
Ahh.
That was really good.

1474
01:10:40,737 --> 01:10:42,262
Yeah, I thought
I was going to have to sneak

1475
01:10:42,305 --> 01:10:45,400
a second supper on my the home.

1476
01:10:45,441 --> 01:10:47,239
{piano playing lightly)

1477
01:10:47,276 --> 01:10:48,869
Would you like to dance?

1478
01:10:51,247 --> 01:10:53,545
I would love to.

1479
01:10:53,583 --> 01:10:54,812
Okay.

1480
01:10:54,851 --> 01:10:59,755
{piano playing lightly)

1481
01:11:02,458 --> 01:11:12,425
I

